{"id":1296,"date":"2011-01-11T06:15:08","date_gmt":"2011-01-11T12:15:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_miracle_balloon_now_hotter.php"},"modified":"2011-01-11T06:15:08","modified_gmt":"2011-01-11T12:15:08","slug":"new_miracle_balloon_now_hotter","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/new_miracle_balloon_now_hotter.php","title":{"rendered":"New Miracle Balloon, now Hotter"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/CMNH_logo.gif\" alt=\"Children's Miracle Network Hospitals Logo, Before and After\"><\/p>\n<p>Originally a televised fundraiser first aired in 1983, Children&#8217;s Miracle Network &mdash; now Children&#8217;s Miracle Network <em>Hospitals<\/em> &mdash; has since raised over $4.2 billion in funds that go directly to over 170 children&#8217;s hospitals. Most impressively, a lot of those billion dollars are raised $1 or $2 at a time through the sale of the paper &#8220;Miracle Balloons.&#8221; This month <a href=\"http:\/\/childrensmiraclenetworkhospitals.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Children&#8217;s Miracle Network Hospitals<\/a> announced its name change along with a new identity done pro-bono by the Cincinnati office of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.landor.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Landor<\/a>.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>The Children&#8217;s Miracle Network Hospitals name is an evolution of the previous and better communicates what the organization does. It helps to clarify the mission, while retaining the equity and recognition earned over decades. Known nationally for the paper Miracle Balloon icons sold during fundraising drives, Children&#8217;s Miracle Network Hospitals&#8217; iconic emblem was also modernized. Landor&#8217;s solution was a simple interpretation of the hot air balloon, keeping the original colors and upward movement, to represent the high hopes for all children that benefit from the organization&#8217;s work.<br \/>Landor Press Release<\/blockquote>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"574\" height=\"352\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/1teQZM2T3_o?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">Brand video, showing many of the identity applications.<\/p>\n<iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"572\" height=\"352\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/20Klok1Xb28?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/><br \/>\n<p class=\"caption\">&#8220;Every Child&#8221; video. Logo animation at the very end.<\/p>\n<p>The previous logo looked like it was done in, well, 1983 but in those more than 25 years it established the red and yellow hot air balloon as a very recognizable icon. The new logo is a lovely evolution and simplification of the original &mdash; although I wonder if the striped design of the previous balloon wasn&#8217;t part of what made it so distinguishable. It gives the organization a much more sophisticated presence and, as importantly, the logo plays really with other partner logos, which is a great asset for a charity. The logo animation, with the balloon floating upwards, may be a tad obvious but you would have to enjoy ripping wings off butterflies to not get a slight sense of hope after seeing the &#8220;Every Child&#8221; video above.<\/p>\n<p>If there is an identity that could use a rounded sans serif, it&#8217;s this one. The effect has to be a soft, accessible organization and this works. I would have chosen something a little more refined &mdash; this one flares a little unflatteringly in some of the characters &mdash; but it wasn&#8217;t my choice obviously. Overall, a great redesign that modernizes the organization.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/CMNH_Letterhead_01.gif\" alt=\"Children's Miracle Network Hospitals\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Stationery.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/CMNH_Billboard_01.jpg\" alt=\"Children's Miracle Network Hospitals\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/CMNH_MiracleBalloon_01.gif\" alt=\"Children's Miracle Network Hospitals\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">The new paper &#8220;Miracle Balloon&#8221; sold to raise funds.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.driskellmade.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Nathan Driskell<\/a> for first tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110111_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110111_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110111_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110111_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110111_config_03.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110111_votes_03.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv3\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/divider_voting_start.gif\" alt=\"Voting Begins\" \/>\n<table class=\"table\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n\t<tr valign=\"top\">\n        <!--VOTE CONCEPT-->\n\t\t<td class=\"table_col\">\n\t\t\t<div id = \"pollDiv1\" style=\"